To To capture household heterogeneity, I incorporate two types of agents: Ricardian households (R), with access to capital markets, and Keynesian households (K), who are credit-constrained. All other agent characteristics, including preferences and subsistence energy needs, are assumed to be homogeneous and are denoted generally by the subscript i.
