3.2 Production
The production side of the economy consists of two types of firms: final good packers and consumption good producers. This is a classical structure deployed in the New Keynesian models. An additional feature of this particular environment is that firms use three factors of production: energy, capital and labour. 

3.2.1 Final good producers/packers 
Final good packers operate in a competitive market. They produce the final good C_t^C by combining a continuum of varieties C_t^C (j)so that: 
y_t=C_t^C=(∫_0^1▒〖((C_t^C (j))^((η_f-1)/η_f ) )di 〗)^(η_f/(η_f-1))	(15)
Standard optimization implies that there exists a following demand function for a variety i: 
C_t^C (i)=((p_t^C (j))/(p_t^C ))^(〖-η〗_f ) C_t^C	(16)
Where we have that:
