And by assumption, good packers do not obtain any profit from their activities. 
3.2.2 Intermediate Goods Producers
In the model, there exists a continuum of final output-producing firms indexed by j∈(0,1) that operate in a monopolistically competitive environment. Hence, each firm produces a single differentiated good and operates as a monopoly in its own market. The firm i produces the final output variety C_t^C (j) using a CES production technology, using energy V_t^E and a capital-labour bundle V_t^KL. In this model, I will deploy nominal friction à la Rotemberg [1982], so the firms pay nominal price adjustment costs (AC(j)) with respect to inflation target π ̅. 
